\N<Onee-chan>Huh? What are you doing in a place like this?

\N<Onee-chan>The bus won't come until evening, you know? The
buses here only come twice a day.
\N<Boku>I'm waiting for an older lady here.

\N<Onee-chan>I see. I'm Harumi. Nice to meet you, Boku-kun.
So, is this 'oba-chan' you mentioned a relative of yours?

\N<Boku>Yeah, that's right. She's my dad's younger sister.
Since my mom is busy with the baby being born, I'll be
staying at this auntie's house during summer vacation.
That's why my dad and I came here by bus.

\N<Boku>But, my dad is so absent-minded, he told me to get
off and it turns out it's one bus stop earlier.

\N<Boku>I tried to just get on the bus and go back, but I
realized I had to go to the next bus stop. Geez, I'm so
hopeless.

\N<Boku>Once we arrive at the foot of the mountain, I'll
call my auntie and have her come pick me up, so wait here.

\N<Boku>Why are you here, Onee-chan? The bus won't come for
a while, right? Did you accidentally come here?

\N<Onee-chan>Hehe. No, no. I was just taking a walk. This
place is my favorite spot.

\N<Onee-chan>And let's take a little break. Since there's
quite a distance to the town from here, let's rest here
before heading back.
\N<Boku>Actually, I was feeling a little lonely by myself...

\N<Onee-chan>Hehe, that's true. It must be boring just
sitting there at your age. But don't worry, it's okay.

\N<Onee-chan>If we go to the town ahead, there's a river, a
lake, and even a ski resort. We can swim, go fishing, and
even if skiing is not possible, we can go grass sledding
during this season.

\N<Onee-chan>Besides, there are many kids around your age,
so it would be nice to make friends and play together.
\# I'm sure it will be a fun summer vacation.

\N<Auntie>I'm sorry, Boku-kun! Did I make you wait? I'm
sorry for making you wait in this heat. My older brother has
always been absent-minded...

\N<Auntie>Long time no see ♥ How have you been? Hehe, you've
grown so much ♥

\N<Boku>See! The other day, when I measured, I had grown 5
centimeters taller!

\N<Auntie>And Harumi-chan, did you stay with Boku-kun? Thank
you.

\N<Onee-chan>No, it was just a coincidence that I happened
to pass by and chat with Boku-kun, but I also had fun.

\N<Auntie>Hehe. Come over to my place next time. I'll give
you some special service.

\N<Auntie>Well then, Boku-kun. Shall we go to Auntie's
house? Shall we take Harumi-chan with us?
\N<Onee-chan>No, I'll sketch a little before going home.

\N<Auntie>Oh, is that so? Well then, see you next time.
Let's go, Boku-kun.
\N<Onee-chan>Oh? Are you going for a walk too, Boku-kun?

\N<Onee-chan>I see. So it's an exploration. Boys are
energetic, huh?
\N<Onee-chan>Oh, Boku-kun. Are you exploring again today?

\N<Boku>Yeah! I'm going to investigate every nook and cranny
of this town!

\N<Onee-chan>Good morning, Boku-kun. Are you going on
another exploration today?

\N<Boku>Hmm, maybe it's because I wanted to see Onee-chan
today.

\N<Onee-chan>Oh, really? ♥ Hehe, thank you ♥ If you'd like,
you can come and play at my art studio too.

\N<Onee-chan>Good morning, Boku-kun. Summer is almost over,
isn't it? Did you enjoy your summer vacation?

\N<Boku>Yeah! It was so much fun! I still have plenty of
summer vacation left, so I'm going to keep playing!

\N<Onee-chan>Hehe, that's right. We have to enjoy it until
the end ♥
